Privacy Policy

Last updated: 08/07/2024

1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use any of our games available on the Meta Quest platform and Steam. By using our games, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. Information We Collect

We do not collect any personal information. Our games do not require you to create an account or sign up in any way.

3. Local Data Storage

The only data stored on your device is related to game settings and preferences. This may include:

    Selected settings (e.g., graphics, sound, controls)

    Progress data (e.g., levels completed, achievements)

This data is stored locally on your device and is not transmitted to any external servers or third parties.

4. Use of Collected Data

The locally stored data is used solely to enhance your gaming experience by:

    Remembering your settings and preferences

    Saving your progress in the game

5. Data Sharing and Disclosure

We do not share, sell, or disclose any information collected from you to third parties.

6. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect the data stored on your device. However, please be aware that no security system is impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

7. Children's Privacy

Our games are not directed towards children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

contact@adventurousstudios.com
